      "cycle_7_assignment": "reframe_apply (added by #635) — `fanops reframe --apply`, the MUTATION phase of the reframe migration: a plan-driven, resumable, rollback-able re-render of clips that ALREADY EXIST. Assigned here, not to S09_render, because S09's members (clip, compose, produce, stitch_render) are the PRODUCTION PIPELINE that turns a moment into a new clip, and this is not in that pipeline — it is an out-of-band corpus migration that CALLS the renderer. Its closest analogue is `paths_rebase`: a one-off, careful, reversible rewrite of stored state across the whole corpus. That is S19's remit exactly. (The read-only dry-run REPORT stays in S18_health_diag; see the note there.)",
